<item>
            <title>[LU-19115] Auto-tuning conns_per_peer requires an explicitly specified NIC interface (ksocklnd_speed2cpp)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19115</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It looks like ksocklnd_speed2cpp will be skipped if NIC interface is not specified,&#160; i.e. we have to specify&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;options lnet networks=&quot;tcp0(eth0)&quot; in lustre.conf to enable this conversion&#160;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; ksocklnd_ni_get_eth_intf_speed(struct lnet_ni *ni)
{
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; struct net_device *dev;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; intf_idx = -1;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; ret = -1;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; DECLARE_CONST_IN_IFADDR(ifa);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* check &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ni has &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; assigned */&lt;/span&gt;
  &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!ni-&amp;gt;ni_net_ns || !ni-&amp;gt;ni_interface) {
  &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; 0;   &amp;lt;---- otherwise it will skip here.
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; }
    ....
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideally it may just do conversion in all cases, i.e. even without the NIC interface specify?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
